Cnidome. Spirocysts (in tentacles), basitrichs (in all tissues), microbasic b-mastigophores (in actinopharynx) and microbasic p-mastigophores (in filament) (Table 2, Fig. 7
J-M
). Basitrichs in tentacles, nemathybomes and filaments are distinguished into two types by their size. No nematocysts in body wall.

The species name was named after Yuji Ise, the collector of both holotype and paratype specimens. Origin of Japanese name: New Japanese name: sugashima-gareba-ashinashi-mushimodoki; 
"gareba"
means rocky seashore, the habitat where this species inhabits.
